I'm all for having decent second-hand market, and the sale of used items for profit would help keep clothing going longer... so it is valued and not discarded without looking worn.

It has potential for the e-commerce platform, and can serve to deter unwise purchases. You can share with others your ill fated clothing choices, and try to help educate. Few tarts would stay if the marketplace becomes a well run community.

The donation centres did a fantastic effect developing this.
We have failed thus far to uptake a regular donation of wares.  The wise among us weep in sadness.
